CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 19, 1958, page A2, reads: "Local 609 Present, as Usual - Always well-represented at the Annual Jefferson Day dinner is Refuse and Salvage Drivers and Helpers Union, Local 609, International Brotherhood of Teamsters, AFL-CIO, and this year was no exception. Left to right, clockwise: William Miller, state workingman's compensation referee; Ted Finch, Anthony Rice, John Finch, Theodore (Ted) Johnson, Andrew Goodson, Theodore (Ted) Brown, Howard Lyons and Steadman Buckley. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, clockwise, left to right: William Miller, Ted Finch, Anthony Rice, John Finch, Theodore "Ted" Johnson, Andrew Goodson, Theodore "Ted" Brown, Howard Lyons, and Steadman Buckley, seated at round banquet table for the Jefferson Day Dinner in the Penn Sheraton Hotel, Downtown
